shared_text:
Lewisville ISD added 31 new photos.
August 19 at 4:32 PM ¬∑

That‚Äôs a wrap on the first day of school!

We hit a few bumps today, but we want to thank our students and families for their patience and grace as we continue to navigate through these unprecedented times.

We are SO grateful for our teachers and staff who have worked so diligently to prepare for this new school year. We know we will face more obstacles along the way, but we promise to do our best to serve our students and families.

We look forward to the day we can see all of your smiling faces on our campuses.

Thank you for being a part of our LISD family. #LISD20

March 9 at 3:54 PM ¬∑

More than 120 athletes and partners from all five Lewisville ISD high schools (Hebron Flower Mound, Lewisville, Marcus and The Colony) participated in the second annual LISD Unified Sports Day on March 9 at Lewisville High School.

The event featured 20 teams playing in a basketball tournament.

Numerous LISD students and basketball coaches served as volunteers and Special Olympics Texas representatives were in attendance.

Rockbrook Elementary added 30 new photos to the album: Miss Texas 2019 Chandler Foreman Visits Rockbrook Elementary ‚Äî with Miss Texas 2019.
February 10 at 4:21 PM ¬∑

Miss Texas 2019 Chandler Foreman visited with all students at Rockbrook Elementary on Feb. 10!

Foreman‚Äôs presentation was about being the best leader you can be. She focused on utilizing bravery, discipline, honesty, positivity and respect to help make that happen. Foreman used a game-show format to get students and teachers involved.

Foreman, who is a senior at the University of North Texas and majoring in Broadcast Media, presented to two groups (3rd-5th grade then kindergarten-second grade).

Thanks to Miss Texas for visiting us for the sixth consecutive year! It is always one of our favorite days.

To learn more about Miss Texas 2019, visit misstexas.org.

Friday, Jan. 24, the City of Lewisville and surrounding communities will hold a funeral procession to honor longtime Lewisville Fire Chief Tim Tittle. Chief Tittle served the Lewisville Fire Department for more than 40 years, becoming a staple in the community and a part of the Lewisville High School Hall of Fame as a distinguished alum.

Please plan on taking alternate routes while traveling through the area. Find further details and a map of the procession here: http://bit.ly/chieftittle.

shared_text:
Lewisville ISD added 81 new photos.
January 21 at 12:15 PM ¬∑

The 27th annual Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. Celebration was held Jan. 20 at Marcus High School‚Äôs Auditorium. The theme was, ‚ÄúOne Human Family: A Better Vision for 2020 and Beyond.‚Äù

The event featured entertainment by more than 75 Lewisville ISD students, including the Central Elementary Hispanic Club Dancers, Lewisville High School Dancers and MHS Choir. Boy Scouts from the LHS feeder pattern made the presentation of the colors. Lt. Col. (retired) Carlen Charleston of Erase Race and Strengthen Ethics (E.R.A.S.E) was the keynote speaker.

The distribution of LISD students‚Äô artwork, essay and photography awards also took place (see the winners here: http://bit.ly/2stKmW0).

Vernell Gregg was honored for her vision in creating the event and commitment to keeping it going, as well as her 39 years of service to LISD.

For more info about the event, visit: mlkofnorthtexas.org.

#MLKDay #LISDBEKIND

PARENT NOTICE | Schools will observe regular dismissal times this afternoon and extended day after school care will remain open as normal.

However, due to the threat of severe weather, after school and evening activities are canceled, including District 6-6A basketball. At this time, other sporting events are continuing as scheduled, but that may change. Campuses will share that information via social media and coaches will communicate with their athletes regarding any changes.

Please note that school and district officials are closely observing the weather forecast and will make adjustments to dismissal procedures as needed to ensure the safety and well-being of all students and staff.

Further updates will be communicated via the district and campus websites and social media.

Read more about the district‚Äôs inclement weather procedures: https://www.lisd.net/weather
